x4freetext: Thulium disc, containing 3.38E+23 nuclei.
Ge detector operated in conjunction with
NaI(Tl) annulus for suppression of Compton scattering
events.
235U fission chamber used to
determine neutron fluence.
Plastic scintillator neutron monitor used to normalize
neutron scattering to fluence measurements.
Ge detector efficiency determined using calibrated
gamma-ray sources.
Corrected for:
. multiple scattering (using code PENHA-B),
. neutron and gamma attenuation (using code NEVES),
. fluence variation over sample due to angular
dependence of neutrons from source reaction.
